<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[166,794,152,234]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[166,290,152,176]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is from the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bradley J Sinclair" authorityYear="2003" box="[698,794,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Brachystomatidae" genus="Ceratomerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulbosus">
<emphasis box="[698,794,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">bulbosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(swollen), referring to the greatly swollen or inflated male hypopygium.
</paragraph>
